018\u20132019)\n* [[Komal Sharma]] as Sugna \u2013 Anjor's foster mother (2018)\n* Neeraj Pandey as Keshav/Kesho \u2013 Anjor's foster father (2018)\n* Astha Singh as Garima Rajvanshi \u2013 Gumaan's wife (2018)\n* Unknown as Rohan Singh Rajvanshi \u2013 Gumaan and Garima's son (2018)\n* Avisha Shahu as Tuntun \u2013 Anjor's friend (2018)\n* Kanika Kotnala as Vatsala Rajvanshi \u2013 Mahendra's wife (2018)\n* Unknown as Madhuri Singh Rajvanshi \u2013 Vijay's wife (2018)\n* Sabina Jat as Advocate Vaani Singh Rajvanshi \u2013 Gumaan's younger sister, Bhagya, Suraj, Vivaan and Ragini's cousin sister (2018)\n* [[Swati Kapoor]] as Naina Bedi \u2013 Colonel's daughter (2018)\n* Abhishek Verma as Mahendra Singh Rajvanshi \u2013 Gumaan's 2nd younger brother, Bhagya, Suraj, Vivaan and Ragini's cousin brother, Vatsala's husband (2018)\n* Unknown as Bheem \u2013 Vatsala's father, Mahendra's father-in-law and Gumaan's rival (2018)\n* Unknown as Sandhya Rajvanshi \u2013 Bhagya, Suraj, Vivaan and Ragini's aunt, Gumaan, Mahendra and Vaani's mother (2018)\n* [[Mahesh Thakur]] as Colonel Yashvant Bedi \u2013 Imli's former gun dealer, Naina's father (2018)\n* Kajal Pisal as Kanchan Bedi \u2013 Colonel's younger sister, Naina's paternal aunt (2018)\n* [[Kiran Janjani]] as RAW Officer Abhay (2018)\n* Abhilash Chaudhary as RAW Agent Vishal \u2013 Abhay's assistant (2018)\n* Ayesha Vindhara as Raksha (2018)\n* [[Keith Sequeira]] as Karan Oberoi \u2013 Chakor and Suraj's business partner (2018)\n* Naren Kumar as Vijay Singh Rajvanshi \u2013 Gumaan's  younger brother, Bhagya, Suraj, Vivaan and Ragini's cousin brother & Madhuri's husband (2018)\n* Micckie Dudaaney as Bachcha Pandey \u2013 Rajeshwari and Vikram's right hand (2018)\n* [[Pratima Kazmi]] as Rajeshwari Devi Singh \u2013 Vikram and Akash's mother (2018)\n* [[Mukul Harish]] as Vikram Singh \u2013 Rajeshwari's elder son, Akash's elder brother (2018)\n* Mahi Sharma as Manju (2018)\n* Sanjay Gandhi as Bhanu Pratap Singh (2019)\n* Jaskaran Singh as Lallan Singh (2019)\n* Maera Mishra as Sonya (2019)\n* Digvijay Purohit as Manoj Sharma \u2013 Sameer's father (2019)\n* Barsha Chatterjee as Jaya Sharma \u2013 Sameer's mother (2019)\n* Prachi Singh as Vanshika Sharma  Sameer's sister (2019)\n\n===Guests===\n* [[Vidya Balan]], to promote [[Hamari Adhuri Kahani]] and [[Kahaani 2]]\n* [[Nawazuddin Siddiqui]], to promote [[Manjhi - The Mountain Man]]\n* [[Ranveer Singh]], to promote [[Bajirao Mastani]]\n* [[Salman Khan]] and [[Anushka Sharma]], to promote [[Sultan (2016 film)|Sultan]]\n* [[Shah Rukh Khan]] and [[Anushka Sharma]], to promote [[Jab Harry Met Sejal]]\n* [[Harshad Chopda]] and [[Jennifer Winget]] to promote [[Bepannah]]\n* [[Karan Wahi]] as himself for special dance performance.\n* [[Krystle D'Souza]] as herself for special dance performance.\n\n==Production==\nIt replaced the long-running series ''[[Madhubala \u2013 Ek Ishq Ek Junoon]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/tv/news/hindi/Udaan-to-replace-Madhubala-in-August/amp_articleshow/39167950.cms|title=Udaan to replace Madhubala in August \u2013 Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-08-08|language=en}}</ref>\nThe show was produced by [[Bollywood]] filmmaker [[Mahesh Bhatt]] and was based on his unreleased movie of the same name.<ref name=\"udaan-actually-for-a-film\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/conceptualised-udaan-actually-for-a-film-mahesh-bhatt/15527187|title=Conceptualised 'Udaan' actually for a film Mahesh Bhatt|date=14 August 2014|work=mid-day|accessdate=15 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"bhatt-s-unreleased-film-udaan\"/>\n\nIt was the fourth longest-running Indian television series of [[Colors TV]] after ''[[Balika Vadhu]]'', ''[[Sasural Simar Ka]]'' and ''[[Uttaran]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/tv/photos/colors-udann-completes-1000-episodes-dheeraj-dhoopar-and-wife-vini-attend-party-401301|title=Colors' Show Udaan completes 1000 Episodes}}</ref> With more than 1300 episodes, it was one of the longest running Indian television series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/television/video/udaan-completes-1000-episodes-entire-cast-attends-the-success-party-1191695-2018-03-17|title=Udaan completes 1000 episodes; entire cast attends the success party}}</ref>\n\n==Crossover episodes==\n*''[[Balika Vadhu]]''\n*''[[Laado 2]]''\n*''[[Dil Se Dil Tak]]''\n\n===Trishakti episodes===\nTri means 3 and Shakti means Power, thus trishakti means Power of Three. In each Trishakti, three serials were broke down into parts and were shown one by one.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Sr No.\n! Air Date\n! colspan=\"4\" | Serials\n|-\n| 1\n| February 19, 2016\n| [[Ishq Ka Rang Safed]]\n| [[Thapki Pyar Ki]]\n| [[Sasural Simar Ka]]\n|-\n| 2\n| March 10, 2016\n| Ishq Ka Rang Safed\n| Thapki Pyar Ki\n| Sasural Simar Ka\n|-\n| 3\n| March 17, 2016\n| Thapki Pyar Ki\n| Sasural Simar Ka\n| [[Balika Vadhu]]\n|-\n| 4\n| March 29, 2016\n| Thapki Pyar Ki\n| Sasural Simar Ka\n| Udaan\n|-\n| 5\n| April 8, 2016\n| Thapki Pyar Ki\n| Sasural Simar Ka\n| Udaan\n|-\n| 6\n| April 21, 2016\n| Ishq Ka Rang Safed\n| Thapki Pyar Ki\n| Sasural Simar Ka\n|-\n| 7\n| May 12, 2016\n| Sasural Simar Ka\n| Udaan\n| [[Swaragini]]\n|-\n| 8\n| May 20, 2016\n| Thapki Pyar Ki\n| Sasural Simar Ka\n| Udaan\n|-\n| 9\n| May 26, 2016\n| Thapki Pyar Ki\n| Sasural Simar Ka\n| Balika Vadhu\n|-\n| 10\n| March 5, 2018\n| [[Laado 2]]\n| [[Dil Se Dil Tak]]\n| [[Savitri Devi College & Hospital]]\n| [[Tu Aashiqui]]\n|}\n\n==Dubbed versions==\nThe series is dubbed into [[Tamil language|Tamil]] as ''[[Poovizhi Vasalile (TV series)|Poovizhi Vasalile]]'' on [[Raj TV]]. It has been dubbed into Telugu as ''Vasantham'' on [[ETV (India)|ETV Telugu]] and [[Malayalam]] as ''Nilapakshi'' on [[Surya TV]]. It is also dubbed into [[Sinhala language|Sinhala]] as ''Dhoni'' on [[Hiru TV]]. It is also broadcast in Bengali as ''Resham Jhanpi'' on [[Colors Bangla]]. The series is translated into Armenian as ''Trichk (\u0539\u057c\u056b\u0579\u0584)'' and is broadcast on [[Armenia TV]]. The Vietnamese dub is ''\u0110\u00f4i C\u00e1nh T\u1ef1 Do'', which airs on Echannel (VTVCab5).\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n{{Armenia TV programming}}\n{{Colors Programmes}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Udaan}}\n[[Category:2014 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Colors (TV channel) series]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Indian drama television series]]\n[[Category:Indian television series]]\n[[Category:Indian television soap operas]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Uttar Pradesh]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|2014 series|1989 series|Udaan (TV series)}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Udaan\n| image                    = Udaan (2014 TV series).jpeg\n| caption                  = <!--Please don't use captions for obvious title cards. See Template:Infobox television instructions-->\n| genre                    = [[Drama]]\n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = \n| developer                = \n| writer                   = [[Robin Bhatt]] <br /> [[Javed Siddiqi]] <br /> [[Sameer Siddiqui]]\n| director                 = \n| creative_director        = \n| presenter                = \n| starring                 = {{ubl|[[Spandan Chaturvedi]]|[[Meera Deosthale]]|[[Vijayendra Kumeria]]|[[Vidhi Pandya]]|[[Paras Arora]]|[[Tanya Sharma]]|Gaurav Sareen|[[Toral Rasputra]]}}\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \"Ye Honslo Ki Udaan Hai\"\n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = India\n| language                 = [[Hindi]]\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 1,352\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = Gurudev Bhalla<br>[[Dhaval Gada]]<ref name=\"Bhatt-at-the-launch-of-Udann\">http://timesofindia.indiati