 web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-mahesh-bhatt-s-unreleased-film-udaan-becomes-a-tv-show-2010177|title=Mahesh Bhatt's unreleased film 'Udaan' becomes a TV show \u2013 Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis|work=dna|accessdate=15 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/tv/news/Shastri-Sisters-and-Udann-cast-visit-the-Andhericha-Raja-Pandal/articleshow/41938271.cms|title='Shastri Sisters' and 'Udann' cast visit the Andhericha Raja Pandal \u2013 The Times of India|work=The Times of India|accessdate=15 September 2014}}</ref> From 2014 to 2016, the show starred child actor [[Spandan Chaturvedi]] who played Young Chakor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/gecs/colors-to-awaken-rural-masses-with-udaan-140812|title=Colors to awaken rural masses with 'Udaan' \u2013 Indian Television Dot Com|author=Anil Wanvari|publisher=|accessdate=15 September 2014}}</ref> It then took a generation leap and from 2016 to 2019, the show revolved around Chakor, Suraj, Imli and Vivaan played by [[Meera Deosthale]], [[Vijayendra Kumeria]], [[Vidhi Pandya]] and [[Paras Arora]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/post-leap-vijayendra-kumeria-play-the-male-lead-colors-udann-160128|title=Post leap, Vijayendra Kumeria to play the male lead in Colors' Udann|last=Team|first=Tellychakkar|work=Tellychakkar.com|access-date=2018-08-08|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.iwmbuzz.com/television/celebrities/udann-boyfriend-dont-time-anyone-else-meera-deosthale/2018/02/22|title=Udann is my boyfriend as I don't have time for anyone else: Meera Deosthale {{!}} IWMBuzz|date=2018-02-22|work=IWMBuzz|access-date=2018-08-08|language=en-US}}</ref> In 2019, the show took another leap and focused on Saanvi aka Anjor and Sameer played by [[Tanya Sharma]] and Gaurav Sareen.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/television/soaps/story/udaan-take-a-leap-vijayendra-kumeria-meera-deosthale-replaced-by-these-actors-1458247-2019-02-17|title=Udaan to take a leap. Vijayendra Kumeria and Meera Deosthale to be replaced by these actors|website=India Today|language=en}}</ref>\n\n''Udaan'' highlighted the issue of [[bonded labour]] in Indian villages.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-i-had-tears-in-my-eyes-when-i-heard-the-script-of-udaan-tv/20140823.htm|title='I had tears in my eyes when I heard the script of Udaan'|date=23 August 2014|work=Rediff|accessdate=15 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/bollywood/udaan-sapnon-ki-based-on-bonded-labour-16543.html|title=Udaan: Little Chakor becomes bonded labour|publisher=|accessdate=15 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n{{copyedit|section|date=April 2020}}\n{{Update section|date=July 2019}}\n<!--Note: Per WP:TVPLOT, this section should not exceed 500 words.-->\nThe story, set in a village named Azadganj begins in 1996. Kamal Narayan Rajvanshi, a wealthy landlord is the head of Azadganj, who makes the most villagers bonded labourers and keeps them like animals. \n\nAlso living in Azadganj are couple Bhuvan Lal Singh and Kasturi. A pregnant Kasturi is devastated when her father Hariya dies in an accident. Having no money, Bhuvan visits Rajvanshi mansion to beg for money from Kamal.\n\nKamal's wife Tejaswini suggests that they keep the child as collateral instead of money. Kasturi and Bhuvan agree; Kasturi gives birth to a daughter Chakor, on the night of full moon. Tejaswini allows them to take her home for eight years, stating that she must be brought back to the mansion to serve.\n\n===8 years later===\n\nChakor is grown-up as an aspiring Marathon runner, but still kept as a collateral. Kasturi and Bhuvan have another daughter, Imli.chakor goes have haveli for the first time chakor don't want to live there she raised voice for her and the villagers's rights against Kamal. She also maintains a friendship with Kamal's nephew Vivaan.\n\nKamal's son Suraj hates Chakor. After a series of events, it is revealed Chakor has a twin sister Chunni and Kasturi give birth to twin daughters her motherinlaw send chunni to Mumbai. Kamal kills Chunni; Chakor learns about Chunni and vows revenge on Kamal for her death.\n\nChakor's Marathon coach Arjun Khanna falls in love with Kamal's daughter Bhagya. The two espace and soon marry. Soon, Chakor leaves Azadganj with Arjun and Bhagya to pursue her dreams but vows to return after ten years, whereas Kamal buries her grandmother Savitri alive.\n\n===15 years later===\n\nChakor makes a comeback, having become a Marathon runner just like she dreamt and desired. She discovers about Savitri's death and gets Kamal arrested though he is later released. Imli is shown to be hating Chakor for her disappearance.\n\nVivaan is an angered man after his father Manohar's death and Kamal married Manohar's wife Ranjana, who is later revealed to have killed Manohar herself to marry Kamal. Suraj is just like and works for Kamal. He often clashes with Chakor.\n\nSoon, Vivaan finds out Ranjana murdered Manohar and severs his ties with her. Though at first, he behaves rudely towards Chakor, their childhood bond slowly revives and they begin to fall in love. Imli begins falling for Suraj and gets pregnant with his child.\n\nSuraj's marriage is arranged to Chakor's co-Marathon runner Tina Raichand. Chakor-Vivaan and Tina-Suraj's wedding is fixed on the same day. Imli accepts Chakor and reveals about her pregnancy. They tell the situation to Tina who accepts their plan not wanting to marry too.\n\nVivaan joins them also. On the wedding, Imli wears Tina's marriage clothes as Tina runs away according to the plan. Suraj learns about this and replaces the brides and grooms with wrong. Due to this, mistakenly Chakor marries Suraj while Vivaan marries Imli. Imli and Vivaan blame Chakor for it Suraj mistreat chakor and blackmail chakor that if she give him the divorce he give that knife to police have imli fingerprint from which he used to murder kamalnaryan meanwhile imli fallen in love with vivan she tell chakor about her feelings chakor with big heart give imli her blessings and also vivan fallen in love with imli imli had a miscarriage \n\n\n\nKamal makes Suraj a labourer and mistreats him, but he is rescued by Chakor and Kamal's mistreating backfires. As Chakor and Suraj's relation becomes strong, they are unable to live without each other. On their first anniversary, Suraj expresses to Chakor he loves her and Chakor realises she loves him too. They decide to start a new life.\n\nElsewhere, Imli tells she is pregnant again but Vivaan is disappointed because of being told in his being a father reports that he can't be a father ever. He starts believing Imli is carrying Suraj's child again. To save Imli, Suraj tells everyone he is her child's father.\n\nChakor, after hearing all this leaves the Rajvanshi mansion and divorces Suraj. It is later revealed that Vivaan's doctor lied about the reports on Ragini's orders. The truth is finally out and Ragini escapes. Imli forgives Vivaan and Chakor apologizes to Suraj; they reunite.\n\nImli miscarries again but doesn't reveal to anyone. Vivaan discovers this and blames her. Imli misunderstands it was Chakor who revealed her miscarriage to Vivaan. She gives a sleeping injection to Vivaan who slips into coma. Now detesting Chakor, she joins hands with Kamal; they stab and throw Chakor in a river with help from goons.\n\n===1 month later===\n\nAs the river reaches [[Varanasi]], Chakor is shown to be saved by a priest, living with him in his house. A doctor reveals that Chakor is pregnant. Brainwashed by Imli, Suraj believes Chakor left him. Chakor contacts Imli who tells her Suraj wants to kill her so she do not return to Azadganj.\n\nLater, Chakor is asked and shifted to live in Ranvijay Singh's house. Ranvijay is an inspector vowing to avenge his father Rajan's death from Rajan's business rival by killing the businessman's son. Suraj visits Varanasi; he and Chakor meet and sort out all things, wanting answers from Imli.\n\nChakor finds out Rajan's business rival is Kamal and Ranvijay is vowing to kill Suraj. She tells Suraj. Ranvijay sees them and realises he wants to kill Suraj. He kidnaps him and tries to forcefully marry Chakor, but they get him arrested and return to Azadganj.\n\nImli tells them that she lied to save them from Kamal, and they forgive her. Kamal kidnaps and pushes Chakor resulting her to fall and thus losing her baby. To avenge for it, Chakor kills Kamal thus also avenging Chunni and Savitri's deaths and making Azadganj independent, but is jailed for 5 years.\n\n===5 years later===\n\nChakor gets released and firstly meets Kasturi, Bhuvan and the villagers. She then visits the Rajvanshi mansion, and learns all of Imli's misdeeds. It is discovered that Imli helped Ranvijay to escape and married him, who hit Suraj on his head leading Suraj to lose his memory, and they appointed him as their servant.\n\nImli is now the head of Azadganj, mistreating the villagers just like Kamal. Tejaswini is being locked by Imli in a secret room of Rajvanshi mansion, while Vivaan is still in coma. Suraj recalls everything and unites with Chakor; they free Tejaswini and go to punish Imli, who shoots Ranvijay to death and escapes. Azadganj gets independence again.\n\n===2 years later===\n\nChakor and Suraj live happily with their family and have a daughter named Saanvi. They start a business, and become rivals with Karan Oberoi, a successful business tycoon. Imli returns to have labouring back in Azadganj and joins hands with the antagonistic Karan to destory Chakor.\n\nLater, Karan dies in an accident, whereas Imli gets exposed as Vivaan wakes up from coma. He has her arrested. Eventually, she is released. Imli's former gun dealer Colonel Yashwant Bedi tries to kill Suraj for a lie. Chakor is about to shoot him to stop him but Vivaan comes in between and dies. Yashwant is arrested. \n\nImli swears revenge for Vivaan's death and kidnaps Saanvi. Imli's goons throw a doll whose size is that of Saanvi in a river, due to which everyone presume Saanvi dead. Suraj blames Chakor for it and severes all ties with her. Chakor, Kasturi and Bhuvan leave Azadganj, while Imli makes Saanvi labourer and hands her to an Azadganj new couple.\n\n===7 years later===\n\nChakor, Kasturi and Bhuvan reside in [[Mumbai]]. Saanvi is being raised by the same couple Sugna and Kesho. She is known in Azadganj with the name of Anjor. Chakor returns to Azadganj for some work. Some goons kidnap Saanvi but Chakor rescues her by defeating them. The two begin to share a friendship, unaware of their relation.Suraj also come back azadganj and meet anjor soon Suraj and chakor find out that anjor is their daughter saanvi and anjor also accept Suraj and chakor\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Spandan Chaturvedi]] as young Chakor Singh (2014\u201316)/ young Chunni: Kasturi and Bhuvan's daughter; Chakor and Imli's sister (2015; dead)\n* [[Meera Deosthale]]/[[Toral Rasputra]] as Chakor Rajvanshi: Kasturi and Bhuvan's daughter; Chunni and Imli's sister; Vivaan's former fianc\u00e9e; Suraj's wife; Anjor's mother (2016\u201319)/(2019)\n* Apurva Jyotir/Darshan Gujrar as young Suraj Rajvanshi (2014\u201315)/(2015\u201316)\n* [[Vijayendra Kumeria]] as Suraj Rajvanshi: Tejaswini and Kamal's son; Bhagya and Ragini's brother; Tina's former fianc\u00e9; Chakor's husband; Anjor's father (2016\u201318; dead)/Raghav Khanna: Suraj's doppelganger (2018\u201319; dead)\n* Tasheen Shah as young Imli Singh (2014\u201316)\n* [[Vidhi Pandya]] as Imli Singh/ Archana: Kasturi and Bhuvan's daughter; Chakor and Chunni's sister; Vivaan and Ranvijay's former wife (2016\u201318, 2018\u201319; dead)\n* Wahib Kapadia as young Vivaan Rajvanshi (2014\u201316)\n* [[Paras Arora]] as Vivaan Rajvanshi: Ranjana and Manohar's son; Chakor's former fianc\u00e9; Imli's former husband (2016\u201318; dead)